<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-circular-sinusoidal">

	<statement>
		<p>
			Let <m>f(t) = \cos(t)</m>.  First, answer all of the questions below <em>without</em> using <em>Desmos</em>;
      		then use <em>Desmos</em> to confirm your conjectures.  For each prompt, describe the graphs of <m>g</m> and <m>h</m> as transformations of <m>f</m> and, in addition, state the amplitude, midline, and period of both <m>g</m> and <m>h</m>.
		</p>
		<p>
			<ol label="a.">
				<li>
					<p>
						<m>g(t) = 3\cos(t)</m> and <m>h(t) = -\frac{1}{4}\cos(t)</m>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						<m>g(t) = \cos(t-\pi)</m> and <m>h(t) = \cos\left(t+ \frac{\pi}{2}\right)</m>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						<m>g(t) = \cos(t)+4</m> and <m>h(t) = \cos\left(t\right)-2</m>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						<m>g(t) = 3\cos(t-\pi)+4</m> and <m>h(t) = -\frac{1}{4}\cos\left(t+ \frac{\pi}{2}\right)-2</m>
					</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</p>
	</statement>

</exploration>
